Description: Corroded copper alloy small amuletic (?) figure of a toad or a frog, originally welded on a base (?) under the rear part, and with a kind of small staple stuck on the left side.
Curator's comments: The Museum register indicates a general reference to the small bronze finds mentioned by W.M.F. Petrie, Tanis ii, Nebesheh and Defenneh, p. 80 § 80, where the item is not clearly described.
Bibliographic references: Petrie 1888 / Tanis. Part II. Nebesheh (Am) and Defenneh (Tahpanhes) (p. 80 § 80) (?)
Leclère and Spencer 2014 / Tell Dafana Reconsidered: The Archaeology of an Egyptian Frontier Town (p.48, p.64, p.181, pl.23)
